<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-54-1212 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper discusses the measures for reducing emissions during the combustionof coal. It is confined to the three substances: dust, NO/sub x/ andSO{sub 2} which are very much in the forefront of environmental protection.Technologies used for the reduction of dust, nitrogen oxide and sulfurdioxides during combustion are evaluated, and the emissions regulationsof the various countries are discussed. 28 refs., 15 figs.</TEXT></DOC>